You shouldn't ever feel like you have to explain why you are getting veneers. I also had my teeth redone over the summer and it was the best thing I've done for myself in a while. I had HORRIBLE anxiety set in mid drilling. I was numb from my cheeks to my throat but could somehow still feel the gritty bits hitting my mouth. I also think that you then realize you're at the point of no return. Your natural teeth are now gone and the fate of your our smile is in the hands of someone else. I'm pretty sure even those who aren't anxious start feeling some type of way once that reality sets in. The permanent porcelain teeth will look soooo much different and be soooo smooth. They were interestingly cold when they first placed them on. I was self conscious about speaking or smiling because it was such a change and I was afraid of being judged. I went to a group in the St. Pete area (Klement Family) and they did an amazing job. I cant wait to see the finished product.

About your conch piercing!!! I had a conch piercing for several months and I too developed a "keyloid" It's actually called hypertrophic scarring, it's just irritation. The conch is a really difficult piercing which is why I took mine out, but I know you're using the sea salt spray to take care of your ears. What I like to do is actually like mix my own sea salt and tea tree oil solution and soak my ear in it. I like to put it in a paper/plastic cup and like, lean my ear into it and sit back up. I keep a towel under it to make sure I don't drip everywhere, and I leave it on for like five minutes. It feels weird and gross, but that tea tree oil and the actual soak will help your piercings so much. I had a flare up with my double helix, and doing a warm sea salt soak every day helped it calm right down. You can also just apply tea tree oil to the bump itself (Test it first to make sure you don't need to dilute it, but it's always better to dilute it anyway) and that will help it go away too.

Also, I'm so excited for your veneers! I need a host of dental work so I can only imagine how excited you must be! 143, hope the piercing tips help!
